# Page layout

See also: **`page-composition.mdc`**, **`design-tokens.mdc`**, **`responsive-design.mdc`**, **`interaction-polish.mdc`**, **`error-handling.mdc`**, **`accessibility.mdc`**. Index: [`skills/SKILL.md`](../../skills/SKILL.md).

**File splitting** → `page-composition.mdc`. This rule owns **spacing rhythm, column alignment, and visual hierarchy** — not which product features your app has.

Golden reference: `src/components/layout/`, `src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx`.

## When to use `AppPageShell`

| Page type | Layout approach |
| --------- | --------------- |
| **App / dashboard / settings** | `AppPageShell` + `PageHeader` — consistent padding and zone rhythm |
| **Marketing / landing** | Often **full-bleed** sections — `width="full"` or a custom layout **without** a global `max-w-3xl` cap |
| **Auth card** | `width="narrow"` or a centered card outside the shell |

**Pick width per route** — do not force every page through `max-w-3xl`. Adjust presets in `layout.constants.ts` for your product.

## Layout primitives

| Component | Purpose |
| --------- | ------- |
| **`AppPageShell`** | Shared page padding, vertical zone rhythm (`gap-8`), optional max-width |
| **`PageHeader`** | Title + description (`gap-1`) + optional action slot |
| **`PageSection`** | Major page zones; optional `border-t pt-8` for phase changes |

```tsx
<AppPageShell width="default">
  <PageHeader title="Items" description="Manage your workspace." action={<Actions />} />
  <PageSection>{/* status / alerts */}</PageSection>
  <PageSection bordered>{/* primary workspace — tabs, tables, cards */}</PageSection>
</AppPageShell>
```

When a route needs full width (e.g. landing hero + feature grid):

```tsx
<AppPageShell width="full">
  <section className="…">{/* hero */}</section>
  <section className="mx-auto max-w-5xl …">{/* optional inner cap per section */}</section>
</AppPageShell>
```

**Do not** hand-roll `py-8` + `max-w-*` on every **app** page — use `AppPageShell` or a deliberate alternative documented in the route.

### Width presets (`AppPageShell`)

Template defaults in `layout.constants.ts` — **rename or change values** to fit your app:

| `width` | Default class | Typical intent (examples only) |
| ------- | ------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `default` | `max-w-3xl` | Standard app content column |
| `profile` | `max-w-2xl` | Focused forms, account settings |
| `narrow` | `max-w-lg` | Auth, compact panels |
| `full` | `max-w-none` | Landing pages, wide layouts |

When app chrome (top nav) and page body share a column, use the **same** `appContentWidthClass` + `appContentPaddingClass` from `@/components/layout`.

## Spacing rhythm

| Level | Gap | Use |
| ----- | --- | --- |
| Page zones | `gap-8` | Between header, alerts, main workspace — `AppPageShell` |
| Section interior | `gap-4`–`gap-6` | Tabs → toolbar → card |
| Status / alerts stack | `gap-3` | Multiple alerts — lighter than primary workspace |
| Title block | `gap-1` | `PageHeader` title + description |
| Dense lists | `gap-2` | Rows, metadata lines |

```tsx
// Bad — flat gap-6; alerts, tabs, and card compete equally
<div className="flex flex-col gap-6">...</div>

// Good — phased zones
<PageSection className="gap-3">{alerts}</PageSection>
<PageSection bordered className="gap-6">{workspace}</PageSection>
```

## Shell alignment

- **`RootLayout` `<main>`** — `pb-10` bottom breathing room; skip link + `#main` (`accessibility.mdc`).
- **Chrome vs body** — when both are constrained, use the **same** max-width — never wider nav over narrower content.
- **Padding** — `px-4 sm:px-6`, `py-8 sm:py-10` on app pages via `AppPageShell` (or match intentionally if full-bleed).

## Visual hierarchy

| Element | Weight |
| ------- | ------ |
| Page title | `PageHeader` `h1` |
| Status / alerts | `Alert` — above workspace, `gap-3` stack |
| Primary workspace | `border-t pt-8` separation |
| Secondary lists | Flat rows — `gap-2`; avoid nested `CardContent` for one metadata line |

```tsx
// Bad — CardContent for a single timestamp
<Card><CardContent><p className="text-xs">3:42 PM</p></CardContent></Card>

// Good — metadata inline
<li className="text-sm">
  <span className="text-muted-foreground">Mar 4, 3:42 PM</span> — Item title
</li>
```

- **Long copy** — `text-pretty` on descriptions.
- **Tinted panels** — semantic tokens, not `text-muted-foreground` on strong washes (`design-tokens.mdc`).

## Mobile

- **Primary CTAs** — `w-full sm:w-auto` on main actions (submit, save, create).
- **Footer actions** — `PageFooterActions` or `border-t pt-6` + stacked buttons below `sm`.
- **Icon controls** — `min-h-11 min-w-11` (`responsive-design.mdc`).

## Loading & empty

- Skeleton **mirrors final structure** — not one gray block (`error-handling.mdc`).
- Empty states **teach** — dashed border + hint; not bare alert text.

## Interaction on actions

- Async buttons: `aria-busy`, disabled while pending, label changes (`Saving…`, `Loading…`).
- Disable when preconditions fail (empty required field, etc.).

## Checklist

- [ ] App routes use `AppPageShell` + `PageHeader` **or** a documented full-bleed layout — no ad-hoc padding drift.
- [ ] Width preset matches route intent (`narrow` / `default` / `full`); landing pages not forced into `max-w-3xl`.
- [ ] Chrome and body columns align when both are constrained.
- [ ] Major phases separated (`gap-8`, `border-t pt-8`).
- [ ] Primary mobile CTAs full-width where it matters.
- [ ] Lists stay flat; skeletons and empty states match structure.
